WCE-INDIA mission is to develop, scale-up and promote enterprise-based solutions to the challenges arising from the impact of energy and globalization on poverty and the environment.

We apply a ‘business or enterprise-based’ approach to deliver self-financing solutions with measurable social benefits that can be replicated, to achieve large-scale impact.

Through our many projects, we are currently;

Supporting the start-up and growth of small and medium-sized enterprises/NGOs in country as a way to reduce poverty:
Bringing down the number of deaths caused by indoor air pollution;
Easing the traffic congestion and pollution clogging up developing country mega-cities and;
Giving developing-country producers improved access to world markets. 

Where appropriate, we seek to deploy WCE-INDIA’s ‘value-adding assets’ – people, knowledge and infrastructure - in ways that help to deliver our charitable objectives.
